INSERT INTO bytes.bytes (id, author_id, title, body, code_snippet, language, embedding, type, is_active, created_at, updated_at) VALUES (
  '48a7ac1f-7ec8-468e-967c-f71bfd787399',
  '00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001',
  $escape$Fastify API Versioning + OpenAPI in One Shot$escape$,
  $escape$Fastify's plugin encapsulation makes versioning a first-class pattern — no middleware gymnastics required. Register each API version as an isolated plugin under a prefixed scope, then attach `@fastify/swagger` and `@fastify/swagger-ui` at the root level to auto-generate a unified OpenAPI spec from your route schemas.

Every route schema you define via `schema: { body, querystring, params, response }` is both a runtime validator (via `ajv`) and a live OpenAPI contributor. Fastify never separates these concerns — validation IS documentation.

Version your routes by prefix (`/v1`, `/v2`) using `fastify.register()` with the `prefix` option. Within each version plugin, define `operationId` in your route schema to avoid collision in the merged spec. Use `{ exposeRoute: true }` on swagger-ui so `/documentation` is auto-mounted.

For deprecation, add `deprecated: true` inside the route's `schema` block — it propagates directly into the OpenAPI output with zero extra config. This keeps your versioning strategy, validation, and API docs in perfect sync across versions.$escape$,
  $escape$import Fastify from 'fastify'
import swagger from '@fastify/swagger'
import swaggerUi from '@fastify/swagger-ui'

const app = Fastify()

await app.register(swagger, { openapi: { info: { title: 'My API', version: '1.0.0' } } })
await app.register(swaggerUi, { routePrefix: '/documentation', exposeRoute: true })

await app.register(async (v1) => {
  v1.get('/users', {
    schema: {
      operationId: 'v1_getUsers',
      response: { 200: { type: 'array', items: { type: 'object', properties: { id: { type: 'string' } } } } }
    }
  }, async () => [{ id: '1' }])
}, { prefix: '/v1' })

await app.listen({ port: 3000 })$escape$,
  $escape$typescript$escape$,
